   104	### Tokenizer / embedder defaults — RESOLVED: engine defaults; custom rides the separate FTS work
   105	
   106	- **Default embedder** = the engine's shipped default (CLS-corrected bge-small today); Memex's `vector:{embedder}`
   107	  is an optional override, absent → engine default. Already how the engine works — no new imposition (Memex uses
   108	  bge-small today).
   109	- **Default tokenizer** = the engine's default FTS5 tokenizer (the one `body`-FTS uses); `fts:{tokenizer}` is an
   110	  optional override, absent → engine default.
   111	- **Custom / per-kind precision tokenizers** are the separately-tracked **≥0.9.x multi-field / per-kind-tokenizer
   112	  FTS** work (`multifield-fts-deferred-0.9.x`), **not a C-1 open item** — C-1 co-lands on the default tokenizer,
   113	  and custom tokenizers graft later via the same idempotent `configure_projections` (same graceful-graft pattern
   114	  as Q4 / Q6a).
   115	
   116	**Net: nothing is genuinely open at the contract level.** The residual P2·S0 work is pure FathomDB-internal 0.9.1
   117	implementation (transaction boundaries) — which every build slice has, and is not a co-design deferral.
   118	
