dev/design/0.7.1-EU-6-FIX-2-design.md:57:| D3 | **TS: hand-written discriminated union in `src/ts/src/index.ts`, NOT in `src/ts/src/binding.ts`.** napi-rs codegen owns `binding.ts`; we don't fight that. The wide `NativeEmbedderEvent` interface stays as a private binding-layer detail. `index.ts` re-declares `EmbedderEvent` as a true union (`DefaultEmbedderDownloadEvent \| DefaultEmbedderCacheHitEvent \| MeanVecPinnedEvent`), `OpenReport.embedderEvents` is typed against the union, and a small mapper in the `openReport()` accessor casts/maps the wide native event to the narrow union. The cast is sound IFF the Rust emitter populates exactly the variant-appropriate fields and leaves the rest null/absent — enforced by AC-FIX2-6's runtime shape-consistency test. | Mirrors the same `binding.ts` (machine-generated wide shape) vs `index.ts` (hand-written public TS surface) seam EU-6 GREEN already uses for every other type (the wide `NativeOpenReport` is similarly re-narrowed by `index.ts`'s `OpenReport`). napi-rs has no first-class support for tagged unions (verified in EU-6 GREEN; see commit `c27712f` discussion). Generating a discriminated union from a Rust enum would require forking napi-derive — out of scope for FIX-2. |
