dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:11:# DECISION BRIEF — scaling FathomDB vector retrieval to 1–2M chunks
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:20:| `dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-vector-latency-roadmap.md` | The full proposal: ranked paths (A>C>B), roadmap scaffold, experiments (E1–E6) with decision rules, trade-offs, upstream extension watch. Appendices A–E: source write-up, clean-room critique, decision arc, code-verified featureset inventory, perf data. |
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:29:1. Shipped vector path is **O(N)** two-phase bit-KNN + f32 rescore; **measured ~1.5 s p50 @ 1M** vs a 300 ms budget (~5× over; ~10× at 2M). Crossover where the 80 ms budget breaks ≈ **50k rows**.
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:30:2. The 1.5 s is **per-row vec0 overhead, not bytes** (32× smaller binary codes bought only **1.37×** speedup; ~150–300× off the popcount floor). ⇒ **int8/Matryoshka are recall levers, not latency levers.**
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:31:3. **Ranked fix: A > C > B.** **A** = a packed/SIMD exact-scan kernel (bypass vec0 per-row overhead) + partition pruning — exact, deterministic, CPU-only, plausibly **<100 ms @ 2M**. **C** = ANN (IVF-via-partition-key), the durability track, needed only if corpus >~5–10M or A can't cover global queries. **B** = relax the budget (hold 300 ms + split CE budget; 700 ms–1 s only as an escape hatch).
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:46:- **If YES (1–2M is real, soon):** the published line has a **real gap** — no vector-latency-at-scale
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:68:5. **Sequence vec0-internal work after/with the 0.8.20 sqlite-vec migration** (it's a predecessor, not a competitor).
dev/design/1-2M-chunk-scaling-DECISION-BRIEF.md:84:- [ ] **Premise = YES / near-term** → I (a) draft the reconciled edit to `ann-index-vec0.md` (overhead-bound, kernel-first; note the falsified <50k assumption), and (b) take the minimum-divergence path to a **Steward** session for scheduling sign-off (E1 + kernel placement).
