dev/design/slice-30-design.md:46:**Justification:** Conservative starting value, equal to `RRF_WEIGHT_VECTOR`. Without R2 per-class delta data we cannot calibrate the graph arm weight. 1.0 is the minimum non-zero contribution; text already dominates at 3.0. The graph arm's purpose is to surface additional *reachable* nodes, not to override the primary signals. A value of 1.0 means the best graph-arm hit (position 0 in the sorted candidate list) gets `1.0/(30+1) = 0.032` — comparable to a rank-1 vector hit.
