dev/design/0.8.18-slice-0-vector-equivalence-publish-design.md:160:| R-VEQ-1 | Probe set (45 probes + **UN-centered f32** reference vectors + embedder identity) persisted at **first vector-kind registration**. **Store f32 only — NEVER persist P1 bits** (bits are recomputed at check time from the uncentered ref + the live mean). **Schema migration SCHEMA_VERSION 18 → 19.** | RED `probe_set_persisted_at_first_vector_kind_registration`: fresh engine → register vector kind → `_fathomdb_embed_probe` has 45 rows `(probe_text, reference_vec f32[384], embedder_name, embedder_revision, dim=384)`, no bit column. RED `step19_migration`: asserts `SCHEMA_VERSION` 18→19 + table shape; fails today. |
dev/design/0.8.18-slice-0-vector-equivalence-publish-design.md:162:| R-VEQ-3a (P1 binary) | Assert the **Phase-1 binary-code flip count** at the **mean-centered** representation `vec_quantize_binary(sign(x − mean_vec))` — the `embedding_bin` codes used by `build_vector_phase1_sql`. | RED `probe_p1_flip_count_matches_embedding_bin`: for stored refs, the probe's P1 bits are byte-equal to the engine's `embedding_bin` production (centered by the live pinned `mean_vec`); a flip beyond the (review-set) count trips. |
dev/design/0.8.18-slice-0-vector-equivalence-publish-design.md:164:| R-VEQ-3c (centering gate + seam) | Centering applies **iff** `identity_requires_mean_centering(identity)` (true only for default `fathomdb-bge-small-en-v1.5`) AND a `mean_vec` is pinned; NoopEmbedder no-op; symmetric ingest+query; un-centered fallback if no pin. **The probe check runs AFTER open-time mean-recovery/requantize + `ensure_vector_partition`** (reads the FINAL live mean), NOT immediately after `check_embedder_profile`. | RED `probe_respects_mean_centering_gate`: MC-required-with-pin ⇒ P1 centered; non-MC/no-pin ⇒ P1 un-centered on BOTH sides. RED `probe_runs_after_mean_recovery`: on a crash-recovered DB that re-pins at open, the check uses the post-recovery mean. |
dev/design/0.8.18-slice-0-vector-equivalence-publish-design.md:165:| R-VEQ-4 | Loud typed refuse-to-serve via **degraded-open** + a **query-time** typed error on the **single choke point**. Open succeeds with `dense_disabled=true` (state re-derived every open). The refusal is a new **`EngineError::VectorEquivalenceMismatch`** (NOT `EngineOpenError` — queries surface `EngineError`), raised at **`search_inner_with_stats`** BEFORE embedding / vector SQL / graph seeding / CE rerank, covering EVERY vector-dependent arm (`search`, `searchExpand`, explain/rerank, graph-arm). An explicit **text-only/FTS-only search path** stays serviceable. Py (pyo3) + TS (napi) get **leaf error classes/codes** (parity with `EmbedderIdentityMismatch`). | RED `divergent_open_is_degraded_not_failed`: open succeeds, `dense_disabled` set. RED `every_vector_dependent_arm_refuses_with_typed_error`: each of search/searchExpand/explain-rerank/graph-arm raises `VectorEquivalenceMismatch` (engine + Py leaf class + TS leaf code), NO silent partial results. RED `fts_only_path_still_serves_when_degraded`: the text-only path returns results. |
