dev/design/0.7.1-EU-6-FIX-1-design.md:52:| D3 | **Test-hooks reinstated for tests via an explicit `maturin develop --features ...` pytest fixture, NOT via pyproject discovery.** | `pyproject.toml [tool.maturin] features` is read by every consumer of `pip install -e .` AND by maturin-action in `release.yml` (it inherits unless overridden by `args:`). Leaving `test-hooks` there couples dev-build feature surface to release-build feature surface. The fix is mechanical separation: pyproject lists only what the release ships; pytest's session-scoped fixture rebuilds the binding with the dev-only features before any test imports `fathomdb._fathomdb`. TS side already has this separation (`build:native` vs `build:native:debug` in `src/ts/package.json:18-19`); only the production script needs `--features default-embedder` added. |
