dev/design/fathomdb-memex-overall-roadmap/03-memex-roadmap-adjustments.md:121:- **What agreement commits Memex to (the frozen, adversarially-reviewed contract):** engine-owned three-axis lifecycle (existence/admission, version-currency via the **already-shipped** `superseded_at` G0 index — NOT a new `is_latest` column, temporal-validity extending edge `t_valid`/`t_invalid` to nodes); mechanism(FathomDB)/policy(Memex) seam; **C-1** — Memex's `EntityTypeSpec` drives the engine `ProjectionSpec` in one registration flow (HARD requirement — couples directly to 0.5.5-A's R-A); **C-2** — `SearchHit.id` becomes a typed `{space,value}` newtype; **+3 verbs** (`transition`, `purge`, `configure_projections`) / **+5 governed types**; **op-store liveness stays OUT of scope** (`__memex_deleted__` remains a permanent op-store convention — resolves 2 of 3 CR-056 encodings); `undelete` naming (never `restore`); Memex deletes its 3 hand-rolled not-live encodings (minus op-store) and stops re-deriving liveness client-side in `fathom_store.py`.
