dev/plans/0.8.6-0.8.16-PROGRAM-SEQUENCING.md:410:- **F-16 — ANN / HNSW is a 2.x item, explicitly NOT 0.8.x (HITL 2026-07-02; reconciled by the Steward).** The vector stage is brute-force (two-phase bit-KNN: Hamming scan to `TOP_K_BIT_CANDIDATES`=192 → exact-f32 rerank), O(N) — it meets the 10k-row p50 gate but misses the 100k/1M budgets. A doc drift had `runs/0.8.x-remaining-todos.md` aspirationally noting "0.8.20 evaluate HNSW" while `plan-0.8.20.md` is **deps-only** (napi + `rusqlite`/`sqlite-vec` majors, F-12) and the authoritative design `dev/design/ann-index-vec0.md` targets post-1.0/pre-2.1. **HITL RULED 2026-07-02: replacing the sqlite-vec O(N) scan with an HNSW/ANN index (usearch/libSQL) is a 2.x item — NOT scheduled anywhere in the 0.8.x line, NOT 0.8.20; 0.8.20 stays deps-only.** Rationale unchanged: target consumers run <~50k rows where the 10k p50 gate is met, and GPU is not the retrieval lever (`[[gpu-not-retrieval-lever-hnsw-at-0.8.20]]`, timing corrected). Reconciled: `remaining-todos.md` §4 corrected; steward memory updated. *Surfaced by the steward readiness audit; ruled by HITL 2026-07-02; reconciled by the Steward.*
dev/plans/0.8.6-0.8.16-PROGRAM-SEQUENCING.md:411:- **F-17 — The DB scale-bound is a 0.9.x arc (0.9.0 *soft* → 0.9.3 *stated*), NOT a 0.8.18 GA claim (HITL 2026-07-02; reconciled by the Steward).** **⚠ REVISED-IN-PART by F-20 (2026-07-07): the scale-bound WORK is pulled INTO the 0.8.x line (0.8.23 *soft* / 0.8.24 *stated*) so 0.8.x is cohesive before 0.9.0; the lower rungs (1.0.0 exit-beta, 1.1.0 hard) still stand, and 0.9.x's role is now OPEN.** The steward readiness/sequencing audit flagged that 0.8.18 "GA-grade shippable" is unbounded on scale while the vector path is O(N) brute-force (HNSW/ANN is 2.x, F-16), and proposed labelling a scale envelope on the 0.8.18 GA DoD. **HITL RULED 2026-07-02: 0.8.18 GA makes NO scale claim; the scale-bound is a staged maturity ladder.** Pre-1.0.0 is **beta** — so 0.8.18's "GA capstone" is *release-engineering* GA (publish machinery + safety gates complete), NOT a maturity/stability/scale guarantee. The ladder: **0.9.0 = *soft* (advisory) scale bound · 0.9.3 = *stated* (firm, tested) scale bound · 1.0.0 = exit beta / first stable · 1.1.0 = *hard* scale bound (a supportable promise for the local-first envelope)** — with **1.0.0 → 1.1.0 deliberately left as break/fix room** before the hard commitment ("we will build our way there"). The 1.1.0 hard bound commits the current exact-search local-first envelope; the **2.x HNSW/ANN work (F-16) later raises the bound** to large-scale. So the "label the GA scale envelope at 0.8.18" option is **declined** — 0.8.18 stays scoped to #5 vector-equivalence + #11-full publish (F-1), and rests on the frozen eu7 + latency gates for its operating point. This is beyond the 0.8.x master horizon; a future 0.9.x roadmap doc will carry the 0.9.0 / 0.9.3 slots when authored (`remaining-todos.md` §4 seeds them). *Ruled by HITL 2026-07-02; reconciled by the Steward.*
dev/plans/0.8.6-0.8.16-PROGRAM-SEQUENCING.md:412:- **F-18 — Memex ranked-needs weighting: OPP-12 (≥0.9.x) is the single major FathomDB-side blocker for Memex; the 0.8.15 dispatcher serves no top-5 Memex need and has ZERO OPP-12 dependency (Steward analysis 2026-07-07; the 0.8.15 resequence is HITL-pending).** Memex supplied a ranked "key needs from FathomDB" (memex `6f7456c` context). **Both P0 items are the OPP-12 record-lifecycle pair:** #1 the **Cause-A typed `SearchHit.id` round-trip** (C-2 / F-8a — typed `IdSpace` + `write_cursor→logical_id`; **verified NOT started** — `SearchHit.id` is `u64`, `stable_id` additive only; **TC-8**), and #2 the **OPP-12 net-new lifecycle build** (existence axis · node-validity · projection registry + EAV/property-FTS · `dense_readiness` · surrogate `logical_id`). #3 (`margin`/V-7) is P1 but **low Memex value** (gap ~0.03; cascade stays OFF regardless); #4 (adjudicator signals) is P2 enhancement (core signals landed); #5 (OPP-1 follow-on) is P3 (ball is Memex-side). **So essentially all remaining Memex need from FathomDB = OPP-12 @≥0.9.x** — a *forward-capability* blocker (Memex runs today on shipped FathomDB), gated behind the 0.8.x tail. **Memex-value critical path:** `0.8.16 (F9) → 0.8.18 (#11-full publish matrix) → open 0.9.0 (C-2 swap + existence axis) → 0.9.1 (projection registry + node-validity + C-1 co-land) → 0.9.2 (breaking-pair publish; Memex consumes)`. **Three consequences:** **(a) New forward edge — F9 (0.8.16) → OPP-12 `rankable` projection role (0.9.1):** F9's signal algebra is the `rankable` ranking contract (0.9.x draft §3), so **0.8.16's F9 must be specced with it in mind**, and 0.8.16 is thereby ON the Memex critical path. **(b) 0.8.15 (in-library dispatcher, OPP-10) is OFF the Memex critical path** — it appears in **none** of the top-5 needs (Memex is the sophisticated L1 driver; the in-library L2 is "batteries for thin consumers"), it is still gated on the **unrun V-7 leg**, and it has **ZERO OPP-12 dependency** (verified: the only "dispatcher" in the OPP-12 contract is the *async projection worker* `lib.rs:876-887`, already shipped — a naming collision with the 0.8.15 *routing* dispatcher; `route_recommend`/`search_routed`/`RouteDecision` appear nowhere in the OPP-12 design docs, and the 0.8.15 plan references OPP-12 nowhere). **HITL DECIDED 2026-07-07: PARK 0.8.15** (§4 row marked ⏸ PARKED) — next commission = **0.8.16**; re-open the dispatcher on a thin-consumer demand signal or after the Memex-critical releases. Parking it is zero-OPP-12-risk (and avoids a future `search_routed`↔`ReadView` retrofit). Focus pivots to **OPP-12**, starting with the **C-1 co-design (TC-7)** run as a bounded two-shot loop with Memex on `dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl`. **(c) New near-term coordination — C-1 co-design timing (TC-7):** Memex's **Commission C (entity-schema-registry) is live 0.5.x work** that builds toward the hard C-1 `EntityTypeSpec→ProjectionSpec` seam; the co-design ADR should be agreed **before** Memex locks Commission C's registry shape, even though FathomDB's build is 0.9.1. **UPDATE 2026-07-07: C-1 CONVERGED** (bounded 2-shot loop; `dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-C1-converged-contract.md`) — the break-if-late `AttributeSpec.index` role hint is already **frozen inert in Memex Commission C** (memex `95ed450`); TC-7 → converged-pending-HITL; **C-1 timing risk retired**. Cross-refs TC-7/TC-8, steward-ledger `seq 36`, memex `6f7456c`, `dev/plans/0.9.x-roadmap-DRAFT.md §3/§5`. *Steward analysis from the Memex ranked-needs list, verified from git; the 0.8.15 resequence + C-1-timing are HITL-pending.*
dev/plans/0.8.6-0.8.16-PROGRAM-SEQUENCING.md:413:- **F-19 — HITL RESEQUENCE (2026-07-07): OPP-12 is PULLED INTO THE 0.8.x LINE and must be DONE before 0.9.0; the 0.8.x micros keep counting up (odd/even); 0.9.0 decouples to the F-17 scale-bound arc only.** **Supersedes the "OPP-12 breaking ⇒ ≥0.9.x" placement** (0.9.x-roadmap-DRAFT + F-18's critical-path line). **Direction (HITL-decided):** (1) **ALL OPP-12 work** — existence axis · node-validity · `ReadView`/read-modes · projection registry + EAV/property-FTS · `dense_readiness` · surrogate `logical_id` · the **C-2 typed `SearchHit.id` swap (TC-8)** — **lands in 0.8.x**, built to DONE before 0.9.0; (2) the 0.8.x micro numbers **keep counting up** under the two-tier **odd/even** rule (even = publishable w/ HITL · odd = OOB label-only · `13` still forbidden); (3) **0.9.0 no longer carries OPP-12** — it reverts to the **F-17 scale-bound arc** (0.9.0 *soft* → 0.9.3 *stated*), opening only **after** OPP-12 is DONE in 0.8.x. This cleanly removes the old OPP-12-vs-scale-bound tension at 0.9.0. **Rationale:** pre-1.0 is beta (F-17) so a breaking OPP-12 surface may publish *within* 0.8.x (build label-only across odd micros → publish atomically at an even micro after 0.8.18's #11-full matrix); "get OPP-12 DONE" is the priority (it is Memex's entire remaining need, F-18). **Prereqs (landed / in-line):** EXP-S substrate (0.8.14 ✓) · Cause-A base (✓) · F9 for `rankable` (0.8.16) · #11-full publish matrix (0.8.18) · C-1 RATIFIED (✓). **CONCRETE ALLOCATION = PROPOSED, pending HITL confirm (Steward 2026-07-07):** OPP-12 slots right after 0.8.18 as **0.8.19 (odd, label-only) = Phase-1** [existence axis · `transition`/`purge` · C-2 swap · schema migration · X1] and **0.8.20 (even, publishable) = Phase-2 + breaking-pair publish** [read-modes/`ReadView` · node-validity · projection registry (C-1 co-land) · `dense_readiness`; pairs with a Memex 0.5.x-successor], **bumping** former 0.8.19 (free-threading/#13-bench)→**0.8.21** and former 0.8.20 (dep-migrations)→**0.8.22**. *(Alt: append OPP-12 at 0.8.21/0.8.22, keeping free-threading/deps at 0.8.19/0.8.20 — but that delays the priority.)* **Knock-ons to reconcile on confirm:** §4/§5 allocation rewrite; C-1 converged-contract landing ref (`0.9.1 P2·S-F` → the new 0.8.x slot); 0.9.x-roadmap-DRAFT (OPP-12 removed, 0.9.0 = scale-bound only, §7 decisions 1/2/4/5/6/8 fold into this resequence). *Direction by HITL 2026-07-07; concrete allocation proposed by the Steward, pending confirm.*
dev/plans/0.8.6-0.8.16-PROGRAM-SEQUENCING.md:415:- **F-21 — HITL BUILD-AUTHORIZED OPP-12 (0.8.19 Phase-1 + 0.8.20 Phase-2); build ≠ adopt; publish stays a separate per-`x.y.z` gate (2026-07-08).** With C-1 RATIFIED both sides and the F-19/F-20 slotting confirmed, HITL **cleared the OPP-12 build gate** for both slots. **What this authorizes:** *building* the full OPP-12 surface — Phase-1 (existence axis · `transition`/`purge` · **C-2 typed `SearchHit.id` swap / TC-8** · surrogate `logical_id` · `SCHEMA_VERSION` migration · X1) and Phase-2 (`ReadView`/read-modes · node-validity · **projection registry, C-1 co-land** · EAV/property-FTS · `dense_readiness` · X1). **What it does NOT do:** (a) **build ≠ adopt** — per-item *adoption* arms (e.g. anything that changes shipped default behavior) remain separately gated; (b) **publish is still a separate explicit HITL call** on the 0.8.20 `x.y.z` (Phase-1 @0.8.19 is label-only regardless); (c) it does **not** reorder the line — **OPP-12 stays in-sequence after 0.8.18** (0.8.16 → 0.8.18 → 0.8.19 → 0.8.20). **Sequencing note (Steward):** building 0.8.19 Phase-1 OOB *now* (parallel to the in-flight 0.8.16) is technically prereq-clear (EXP-S/Cause-A/C-1 all met) BUT would run **two concurrent `SCHEMA_VERSION` migrations** (F9 step-18 @0.8.16 ∥ OPP-12 @0.8.19) on the shared tree — a real collision hazard — so the Steward recommends **in-sequence** unless HITL elects to parallelize with explicit migration-ordering. **Ladder drift flagged (follow-up, NOT physically-hard — slots are 2 releases out):** `plan-0.8.19.md` still holds the **pre-F-19 "free-threading + benchmark harness"** content and `plan-0.8.20.md` the **"Library Sweep / dep-migrations"** content (both now allocated to **0.8.21 / 0.8.22** by F-19/F-20). The **OPP-12 Phase-1/Phase-2 ladders must be authored** (as the slot approaches, per F-10) and the free-threading/deps ladders **re-homed to `plan-0.8.21.md` / `plan-0.8.22.md`**; until then those two filenames mis-describe their slot. *Build-authorization by HITL 2026-07-08; recorded + drift flagged by the Steward.*
