dev/notes/context-research-agentic-best-practices.md:182:- **C1: Embedding RAG vs agentic grep.** _tmp_ says "do not make embedding the substrate"; _tmp2_ says "no local vector index"; _tmp3_ says "hybrid: lexical + semantic + structural." Resolution: _for a single local repo on a typed Rust + Python + TS codebase, grep + glob + read + tree-sitter map is sufficient and matches Anthropic's published direction. Embeddings become useful at multi-repo / cloud scale or for pure-prose corpora._ For FathomDB now: skip vector index; revisit if cross-repo agent search becomes a goal.
