dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3510:The patch adds validity-aware search, but the vector branch filters validity after the candidate limit and the graph arm can evaluate a different default `now` than the other arms. These are correctness issues for the newly introduced search view behavior.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3514:- [P2] Apply validity before limiting vector candidates — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:9165-9169
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3515:  When dense search is enabled, this validity predicate is only applied while hydrating the already-limited vector candidates. If the nearest `final_limit` vector rows are expired/future-window nodes, they consume the KNN slots and are then dropped here, so valid rows ranked just below the cutoff are never considered and search can return too few or no valid hits. The validity filter needs to participate in the vector candidate selection before the `ORDER BY ... LIMIT` cutoff, or the vector branch needs a backfill/overfetch strategy.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3518:  For default views (`valid_as_of == None`) with `use_graph_arm=true`, this recomputes `current_epoch_seconds` inside the graph arm instead of reusing the `now_param` already resolved for the vector/text arms in `read_search_in_tx`. If the query crosses a validity boundary between those calls, different search arms evaluate different instants, causing nondeterministic inclusion/exclusion of boundary-window nodes. Pass the resolved instant into the graph arm or freeze it into the view before dispatching.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3519:The patch adds validity-aware search, but the vector branch filters validity after the candidate limit and the graph arm can evaluate a different default `now` than the other arms. These are correctness issues for the newly introduced search view behavior.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3523:- [P2] Apply validity before limiting vector candidates — /home/coreyt/projects/fathomdb-worktrees/orch-0.8.20-s15/src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:9165-9169
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3524:  When dense search is enabled, this validity predicate is only applied while hydrating the already-limited vector candidates. If the nearest `final_limit` vector rows are expired/future-window nodes, they consume the KNN slots and are then dropped here, so valid rows ranked just below the cutoff are never considered and search can return too few or no valid hits. The validity filter needs to participate in the vector candidate selection before the `ORDER BY ... LIMIT` cutoff, or the vector branch needs a backfill/overfetch strategy.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-15b-fix-2-rereview-20260720T205344Z.log:3527:  For default views (`valid_as_of == None`) with `use_graph_arm=true`, this recomputes `current_epoch_seconds` inside the graph arm instead of reusing the `now_param` already resolved for the vector/text arms in `read_search_in_tx`. If the query crosses a validity boundary between those calls, different search arms evaluate different instants, causing nondeterministic inclusion/exclusion of boundary-window nodes. Pass the resolved instant into the graph arm or freeze it into the view before dispatching.
