dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-5-fix-4-5-delta-20260720T022544Z.log:2751: {"ts": "2026-07-19T04:09:21.079Z", "seq": 32, "kind": "observation", "summary": "ROOT CAUSE: the eu7 harness CANNOT COMPLETE ON CPU on this box -- BATCH=256 exceeds its own hardcoded 600s drain timeout at the measured embed rate. Measured at 4ca70ba6 by bisecting N (three runs): n=7667 FAILED, n=200 FAILED, n=20 PASSED. All three failures are identical: panic at eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs:414 'seed drain (batch): Scheduler' == engine.drain(600_000) -> wait_for_idle timed out -> EngineError::Scheduler. THE WORKER IS NOT WEDGED: n=20 passed cleanly (exit 0, vector_stage recall@10 = 1.0000, 258.54s) so the embed/projection path is FUNCTIONALLY CORRECT. It is THROUGHPUT. The n=20 run reports seed_ms=111670 for 20 docs = 0.179 docs/sec, which is ~7.3x SLOWER than the 1.3 docs/sec the harness docstring assumes (:97-99). At 0.179 docs/s a BATCH of 256 needs ~1430s, so it can NEVER drain inside the hardcoded 600_000 ms -- the harness is STRUCTURALLY unable to run here regardless of N, because failure happens on the FIRST batch. Full 7667-doc seed would need ~11.9 HOURS even if the timeout were raised. NOT a weights problem (cache complete: config.json + tokenizer.json + model.safetensors present) and not CPU contention (load 4.5 of 24 cores). OPTIONS for Slice 40: (a) reduce BATCH 256 -> 64 (64/0.179 = 358s, fits inside 600s) or make BATCH/timeout env-tunable -- minimal, surgical, does NOT change measurement semantics; (b) raise the drain timeout and accept a ~12h CPU run; (c) investigate the 7x throughput shortfall vs the documented rate, which may itself be a real CPU-embed regression worth catching. RECOMMEND (a)+(c). NOTE THE TENSION: TC-12 forbids running eu7 on GPU for comparability, and CPU cannot finish -- so R-20-EU7 has NO runnable path until this is fixed. Slice 40 must not treat this as optional. SIDE-EFFECT HAZARD: the harness WRITES dev/plans/runs/eu7-latest-measurements.json into the repo on every run, so a reduced-N scouting run silently produces a file that LOOKS authoritative (the n=20 run wrote recall=1.0000 there). Do not commit it from a scouting run.", "cx": "TC-19", "release": "0.8.20", "slice": "40", "status": "OPEN", "refs": ["file:src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/eu7_real_corpus_ac.rs", "seq:26"]}
