dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-5-fix-7-rereview-20260720T032538Z.log:8146: {"ts": "2026-07-20T02:14:53.190Z", "seq": 45, "kind": "observation", "summary": "WRITE/READ PROVENANCE ASYMMETRY -- the 'NO SDK EXPOSURE' erasure gap, now measured. 0.8.20 makes provenance structurally MANDATORY on write (SourceId newtype), but PySearchHit.source_id is populated ONLY for graph-arm hits and is None for every two-arm (text/vector) hit -- documented at src/rust/crates/fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:537-539. So a caller can be forced to supply provenance yet cannot read it back on an ordinary search hit. Measured consequence: BOTH remaining Python suite failures (test_option2_elps_pipeline::test_build_fathomdb_elps_path_uses_ingest_with_extractor and test_verify_embed_db::test_complete_embed_is_queryable) are caused by this -- _doc_id_of falls through the 'if sid:' branch because source_id is None, reaching int(sh.id) which has raised TypeError since 0.8.19 made SearchHit.id an IdSpace (C-2). ONE read-side fix (expose source_id on all arms) likely closes BOTH. Verified pre-existing: identical failures on origin/main f22e4947 in an isolated A/B clone; _doc_id_of is byte-identical on main.", "id": "TC-31", "release": "0.8.20", "slice": "5", "status": "open", "refs": ["git:9c87d758"]}
