dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-5-fix-1-rereview-20260719T234803Z.log:7790:The patch adds important erasure functionality, but the new provenance doctor misclassifies a known unerasable edge shape, and source erasure can time out when vector projection work is pending. These are actionable correctness issues in the new/changed behavior.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-5-fix-1-rereview-20260719T234803Z.log:7798:  For `erase_source`/`excise_source` called right after writing a vector-indexed row, freezing before the first `drain` can strand work that has not yet been queued: `wait_for_idle` sees pending DB work, but the frozen dispatcher cannot scan and enqueue it, so the erasure waits for the full lifecycle timeout and returns `Scheduler`. `purge` already does an unfrozen drain before freezing for this reason; the shared source erasure path needs the same ordering.
dev/plans/runs/codex/0.8.20/slice-5-fix-1-rereview-20260719T234803Z.log:7799:The patch adds important erasure functionality, but the new provenance doctor misclassifies a known unerasable edge shape, and source erasure can time out when vector projection work is pending. These are actionable correctness issues in the new/changed behavior.
