dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl:1:{"ts": "2026-07-08T00:44:21.753Z", "seq": 1, "kind": "protocol", "summary": "OPP-12 C-1 co-design — BOUNDED TWO-SHOT LOOP. Purpose: converge C-1 (Memex EntityTypeSpec DRIVES engine ProjectionSpec; one registration flow) to a ratifiable contract BEFORE Memex Commission C (live 0.5.x entity-schema-registry) locks its AttributeSpec shape (TC-7). Rounds (capped at 2, learn from OPP-12 seq-1->13 marathon): SHOT 1 = FATHOM opens (ProjectionSpec surface + proposed EntityTypeSpec->ProjectionSpec mapping + ownership seam + <=6 convergence questions + co-land/timing ask). SHOT 2 = MEMEX answers Q1-Q6 + posts EntityTypeSpec/AttributeSpec shape + R-A constraints; FATHOM reconciles -> converged C-1 contract, RATIFIED-pending-HITL. If not converged in 2 rounds: ESCALATE to HITL (do not spiral). Voices FATHOM (steward-owned per N-4) + MEMEX; HITL gates FATHOM content before Memex routing; NO memex push. Tools: ledgerwrite to append, ledgerwatch to read (per HITL discipline). This sub-ledger lives fathomdb-side (dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/); Memex reads/appends locally.", "cx": "C-1", "decider": "steward", "opp": "OPP-12", "voice": "FATHOM", "refs": ["opp:OPP-12", "file:dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-C1-shot1.md"]}
dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl:2:{"ts": "2026-07-08T00:44:21.780Z", "seq": 2, "kind": "proposal", "summary": "SHOT 1 (FATHOM opens) — C-1 EntityTypeSpec->ProjectionSpec co-design. Full text: OPP-12-C1-shot1.md. ProjectionSpec {name, roles:Set<{filterable,rankable,searchable}>, fts?:{tokenizer}, vector?:{embedder}} via configure_projections(spec,drop?), idempotent diff+backfill, projecting from a net-new engine EAV+property-FTS, wrapping the shipped EXP-S per-kind seam (TC-1); async worker already exists (engine:876-887). Proposed mapping: AttributeSpec.key->ProjectionSpec.name; py_type scalar->filterable; str free-text->searchable+fts; graded dial->rankable (F9-gated ~0.8.16); relationships->typed-edge filterable. VERIFIED GAP: Memex AttributeSpec carries NO role field (EAV=group/key/value) -> role source must be co-designed.", "cx": "C-1", "opp": "OPP-12", "shot": "1", "status": "posted-pending-hitl-review", "voice": "FATHOM", "refs": ["file:dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-C1-shot1.md", "opp:OPP-12"], "body": "CONVERGENCE QUESTIONS FOR MEMEX (bounded, answer in SHOT 2):\nQ1 (highest leverage) Role source: does AttributeSpec carry an explicit optional role hint (index: Set[ProjectionRole]) with engine py_type-inference as default when absent? ProjectionSpec needs a role source and has none. RECOMMEND: add the optional field NOW in Commission C -- adding it post-lock re-serializes every persisted WMEntityTypeSpec.\nQ2 EAV convergence: converge on ONE engine-owned EAV (Memex stops writing app-side WorldModelEntityAttribute) or does the projection read FROM Memex's governed-node EAV? 'Converges' is named with no mechanism (under-specified both sides).\nQ3 Idempotent re-registration + drift authority: confirm ENGINE is the sole projection authority via configure_projections diff (Memex never runs a 2nd projection registry); incompatible change (embedder/tokenizer swap on an existing name) surfaces a destructive delta requiring explicit drop -- accepted?\nQ4 provisional/promotion: do provisional=True types get projections immediately (adaptive-loop recall) or only on promote()? If immediate, does a rejected provisional trigger a projection drop (rebuild churn)?\nQ5 R-A persist boundary: PROPOSAL -- Memex persists the spec (WMEntityTypeSpec); the engine ProjectionSpec is a DERIVED cache re-driven idempotently on boot; engine never persists a spec Memex can't re-derive -> one durable source of truth, no 2nd persistent registry to sync. Confirm.\nQ6 rankable/F9 + surrogate id: (a) F9 lands ~0.8.16; can C-1 co-land (0.9.1) ship filterable+searchable only, rankable grafting when F9 lands? (b) how does EntityTypeSpec.id_prefix reconcile with the engine-minted surrogate logical_id for entities that begin anonymous?\n\nCO-LAND / TIMING ASK: Freeze NOW in Commission C (does NOT foreclose C-1): EntityTypeSpec/AttributeSpec shape, JSON serialization, R-A persistence, register() single entry point. ONE forward-compat ask: land the optional per-AttributeSpec role hint (Q1) in Commission C now -- the only field whose later addition is a breaking re-serialization. Must WAIT for FathomDB 0.9.1: configure_projections/ProjectionSpec, engine EAV+property-FTS, dense_readiness. DECISION FORCED THIS LOOP: agree Q1 (role hint) + Q5 (engine-as-derived-cache) before Commission C locks AttributeSpec; Q2/Q3 may co-design to the 0.9.1 P2-S0 ADR but flag open now so neither side over-builds an EAV the other discards."}
dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl:3:{"ts": "2026-07-08T01:15:42.471Z", "seq": 3, "kind": "proposal", "summary": "SHOT 2 (MEMEX answers) — C-1 EntityTypeSpec->ProjectionSpec. Q1 AGREED (option A): optional AttributeSpec.index:Set[ProjectionRole] LANDED inert in Commission C (memex feat/0.5.5a-entity-registry @ 95ed450; byte-identical, persist round-trip tested; the one break-if-later field, carried while fresh). Q3 AGREED (engine sole projection authority via configure_projections diff; incompatible change -> destructive delta requiring explicit drop). Q5 AGREED (Memex persists the spec; engine ProjectionSpec = derived boot cache re-driven idempotently; drift resolves TO the Memex spec; one durable source). Q2/Q4/Q6 answered in the Memex ADR (see body + ref). C keeps moving; no EAV over-build; nothing built now (build != adopt).", "cx": "C-1", "opp": "OPP-12", "shot": "2", "status": "posted-pending-fathom-reconcile", "voice": "MEMEX", "refs": ["memex:dev/design/entity-schema-registry/ADR-C1-eav-projection-lifecycle.md", "seq:2"], "body": "Q2/Q4/Q6 (full detail + file:line grounding in the Memex ADR at memex repo dev/design/entity-schema-registry/ADR-C1-eav-projection-lifecycle.md):\n- Q2 (EAV convergence): ONE engine-owned EAV + property-FTS as end-state, sequenced NO-over-build. 0.5.x interim = attributes stay a nested dict on the governed WMEntity node (fathom_store.py:4635); Commission C does NOT build a standalone persisted attribute node/table. 0.9.1 co-land = engine builds EAV+property-FTS once, Memex repoints set_entity_attribute onto the governed engine-EAV verb, retires the interim; breaking + no data migration. No property-level projection until 0.9.1 (rides body-FTS + R-B generic read) = the plan-C section-7 boundary, not a gap.\n- Q4 (provisional/promotion projection timing): tier by cost. Cheap same-transaction (filterable, searchable->FTS) build immediately for provisional types (adaptive-loop recall); expensive searchable->vector (async + dense_readiness) defers to promote(); rejected provisional drops only the cheap projections (no embedding rebuild-churn). Memex owns the promotion gate; engine executes build/drop.\n- Q6a (rankable/F9): co-land filterable+searchable at 0.9.1; rankable is graceful-absent -- Memex MAY declare rankable roles now; engine defers any rankable projection it cannot yet honor (F9 ~0.8.16), grafting on the next idempotent configure_projections. No rankable role blocks a co-land.\n- Q6b (id_prefix vs surrogate id): id_prefix names the IdSpace/namespace (Memex vocab); engine mints the opaque surrogate logical_id VALUE within it for anonymous entities. Typed carrier (l:/h:/p: -> IdSpace newtype) rides OPP-12 C-2 (lands-together with the Cause-A SearchHit.id swap, >=0.9.x; additive stable_id base landed / typed swap not started = TC-8). C-1 needs only the space/value split.\n\nMEMEX CODE-VERIFICATION REFINEMENTS (reconcile against these -- verified @ 566a40d/95ed450):\n1. WorldModelEntityAttribute ALREADY EXISTS as a read-materialized Pydantic DTO (models/world_model.py:32; synthesized on read in fathom_facade.py:1601-1633; writer fans out to set_entity_attribute). It is NOT a persisted table -> premise holds; the forbidden over-build = do NOT promote this DTO into a stored attribute node/table.\n2. NO provisional/promote() gate exists in Memex today (EntityTypeSpec = name/id_prefix/attributes/relationships only). Q4 tiering + 'Memex owns the promotion gate' is a DESIGN COMMITMENT for the co-land, not extant machinery.\n3. id_prefix is a uniform WM_ENTITY constant across all seeds today, not yet a per-type IdSpace; Q6b is the intended future use.\n\nDeferred to the joint P2.S0 ADR (flag, do not resolve here): register->derive->configure_projections atomicity (Memex's sole requirement = idempotent crash-safe boot re-derive so partial apply heals next boot); concrete tokenizer/embedder defaults.\n\nFATHOM to close the loop (SHOT-2 second half): reconcile/confirm Q2/Q4