dev/research/personal-agent-database-market-2026-07-02.md:115:| 11 | Constructive Agentic DB (agentic-db) | Open-sourced, purpose-built Postgres schema/architecture that gives agents long-term memory, a knowledge graph, and a personal CRM 'world model' inside a single database. | <https://www.prnewswire.com/news-releases/constructive-open-sources-agentic-db-the-postgres-memory-layer-for-ai-agents-302755269.html> | Five retrieval modes on every text-bearing table: pgvector semantic search, BM25 statistical ranking, weighted full-text search, trigram fuzzy matching, and PostGIS spatial queries; Auto-embedding pipeline via Postgres triggers + Ollama to keep embeddings fresh; 'World model' personal CRM / life-OS: contacts, companies, deals, events, projects, goals, habits linked by 25+ cross-domain junctions; Declarative rules / behavioral policies as trigger-action governance layer; Task orchestration priority queue plus runtime observability (logs, metrics, event bus) |
dev/research/personal-agent-database-market-2026-07-02.md:223:All 12 products were verified by fetching their live pages (GitHub READMEs, vendor blogs, or the PR Newswire release). The Constructive Agentic DB Morningstar mirror returned HTTP 403, so features were confirmed via the PR Newswire original and it-brief coverage. Deliberately excluded the well-known incumbents (Mem0, Zep/Graphiti, Letta/MemGPT, LangMem) and the raw vector DBs named in the prompt (Pinecone, Weaviate, Qdrant, Chroma, Milvus, LanceDB) since those are already-known reference points — though note LanceDB is actively marketing itself as 'the natural memory layer for OpenClaw' (<https://www.lancedb.com/blog/openclaw-lancedb-memory-layer>) with an Add/Update/Delete/None write-time loop, and Cognee/Constructive use Qdrant/Weaviate/pgvector/LanceDB as pluggable backends. Additional unverified candidates worth a follow-up pass: vstash (arxiv 2604.15484, single-file SQLite adaptive-RRF with IDF weighting + MMR — appears to be a research prototype rather than a shipped product); OpenMemory (MCP-based personal memory layer); rohitg00/agentmemory (BGE-small on-device via @xenova/transformers); MindLock (IndexedDB local mode); and Potpie ($2.2M pre-seed Feb 2026, codebase-to-Neo4j knowledge graph — adjacent, code-focused rather than general personal memory). FathomDB's own consumers (Memex, Hermes, OpenClaw) recur in this ecosystem — ClawMem, LanceDB, and Cognee all explicitly target OpenClaw/Hermes, confirming those as real integration targets. Several SQLite-based projects cite LongMemEval / LongMemEval-S as the benchmark of record (ai-memory-mcp 97.8% R@5), which is directly relevant to FathomDB's recall/precision gating work.
