dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl:10:{"ts": "2026-07-18T16:01:44.333Z", "seq": 10, "kind": "decision", "summary": "FATHOM -> MEMEX notification (OPP-12 cross-repo contract amendment; HITL-approved '#9'). structural-lifecycle-contract.md §2(ii) is OVERRULED for the anonymous/doc-seeded class -- HITL-ratified 2026-07-12 (pin A; TC-11/F-23 guardrail DISCHARGED; master F-25; LANDED origin/main a197da7c). RULING: anonymous/doc-seeded SearchHits stay h:<content-hash> PERMANENTLY -- the anonymous-surrogate logical_id leg (previously F-23/1a 'deferred to Phase-2') is CANCELLED, NOT deferred. A surrogate serves ONLY registry-admitted GOVERNED entities, minted at write time; a stored row's id-space is NEVER re-derived (no backfill / no forward-mint / no split). GROUNDS (code-verified): an opaque surrogate is not re-derivable from content, so re-ingesting identical content would mint a DIFFERENT id and destroy the re-ingest-stable content-addressed identity h: provides (same bytes => same handle -- gold keying, telemetry result_stable_ids, explain-correlation); derive_logical_id=SHA256('kind:name') is a natural-key HASH, not the opaque surrogate §1.2 requires (§2:98 names it a separate mechanism); §2(ii) has NO Memex consumer (the contract itself states Memex's lifecycle problem is closed by (i) alone); the shipped C-2 IdSpace is already TOTAL, so h: IS an address. IMPACT ON MEMEX = NONE: SearchHit.id values are byte-unchanged (h: stays h:; to_prefixed() == prior stable_id) and C-1 (EntityTypeSpec->ProjectionSpec) is UNAFFECTED and needs NO re-ratification -- this narrows ONLY the §2(ii)/surrogate mechanism. ADJACENT (Memex-relevant): REQ-037 lawful-erasure carve-out HITL-APPROVED 2026-07-12 -- erase_source(source_id) ships as an SDK lifecycle verb in 0.8.20 Phase-2 (the provenance/h:-axis erasure counterpart to purge on the l: axis); excise_source stays CLI-only. Authority reconciled: §2(ii) OVERRULED, README:108 struck, api-surface:64 surrogate leg CANCELLED; design of record dev/design/0.8.20-erasure-and-h-end-state-v4.md; plan-0.8.20 de-staled+authored. HITL-first per standing rule. NO memex push (fathomdb-only).", "cx": "pin-A-§2ii-overrule", "decider": "hitl", "opp": "OPP-12", "status": "pin-A-overruled-ratified-2026-07-12-memex-notified", "voice": "FATHOM", "refs": ["git:a197da7c", "file:dev/design/0.8.20-erasure-and-h-end-state-v4.md", "seq:9"]}
