dev/design/0.8.18-slice-0-vector-equivalence-publish-design.md:202:| R-REL-4f (npm platform contract — concrete topology) | Convert `src/ts/package.json` from the current SINGLE `fathomdb` pkg (`files:[dist, fathomdb.*.node]`) to the standard **napi per-platform split**: a thin main `fathomdb` package whose loader (`index.js`) `require`s the matching platform package and **throws a clear "unsupported platform" error if absent** (never a silent runtime crash); per-platform binary packages named `@fathomdb/fathomdb-<target>` (e.g. `-linux-x64-gnu`, `-darwin-arm64`, `-win32-x64-msvc`) each carrying `os`/`cpu` + the one `.node`, wired as **`optionalDependencies`** of the main package (npm skips incompatible ones at install). **0.8.18 publishes ONLY `@fathomdb/fathomdb-linux-x64-gnu` + the main package under a non-`latest` dist-tag**; the follow-on orchestrator publishes the remaining platform packages + promotes `latest`. Add the per-platform publish jobs to `release.yml` (gated to linux-x64-gnu for this tag, R-REL-4e). | RED-ish `npm_platform_split_contract`: a mac/win install of the 0.8.18 version resolves NO linux `.node` (skipped optionalDep) and the loader throws "unsupported platform" at require-time (not a runtime segfault); the dist-tag is not `latest`. The split topology + linux-x64-gnu-only-for-0.8.18-under-a-non-`latest`-dist-tag is the **decided design**; the HITL confirms only the specific dist-tag label (e.g. `next`) and signs the publish itself — NOT a re-decision of the topology. |
