umers"), it is still gated on the **unrun V-7 leg**, and it has **ZERO OPP-12 dependency** (verified: the only "dispatcher" in the OPP-12 contract is the *async projection worker* `lib.rs:876-887`, already shipped — a naming collision with the 0.8.15 *routing* dispatcher; `route_recommend`/`search_routed`/`RouteDecision` appear nowhere in the OPP-12 design docs, and the 0.8.15 plan references OPP-12 nowhere). **HITL DECIDED 2026-07-07: PARK 0.8.15** (§4 row marked ⏸ PARKED) — next commission = **0.8.16**; re-open the dispatcher on a thin-consumer demand signal or after the Memex-critical releases. Parking it is zero-OPP-12-risk (and avoids a future `search_routed`↔`ReadView` retrofit). Focus pivots to **OPP-12**, starting with the **C-1 co-design (TC-7)** run as a bounded two-shot loop with Memex on `dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-sub-ledger.jsonl`. **(c) New near-term coordination — C-1 co-design timing (TC-7):** Memex's **Commission C (entity-schema-registry) is live 0.5.x work** that builds toward the hard C-1 `EntityTypeSpec→ProjectionSpec` seam; the co-design ADR should be agreed **before** Memex locks Commission C's registry shape, even though FathomDB's build is 0.9.1. **UPDATE 2026-07-07: C-1 CONVERGED** (bounded 2-shot loop; `dev/design/record-lifecycle-protocol/OPP-12-C1-converged-contract.md`) — the break-if-late `AttributeSpec.index` role hint is already **frozen inert in Memex Commission C** (memex `95ed450`); TC-7 → converged-pending-HITL; **C-1 timing risk retired**. Cross-refs TC-7/TC-8, steward-ledger `seq 36`, memex `6f7456c`, `dev/plans/0.9.x-roadmap-DRAFT.md §3/§5`. *Steward analysis from the Memex ranked-needs list, verified from git; the 0.8.15 resequence + C-1-timing are HITL-pending.*
