    13	---
    14	
    15	## 1. The two surfaces serve distinct User Needs
    16	
    17	| | **G10 `search_filtered`** | **G4 `read.list`** |
    18	| --- | --- | --- |
    19	| User need | "Find relevant memories about **X**, **but only from source Y / kind K / after date Z / status S**." | "**List all** my open to-dos." "Give me **all** products rated >4★." |
    20	| Shape | A *constraint on a ranked hybrid/semantic search* (vector-KNN + RRF, optionally CE-rerank). | A *typed enumeration* over active canonical nodes of a `kind`. No ranking, no vectors. |
    21	| Mechanism | Indexed **pre-KNN** filter over vec0 metadata columns — narrows the candidate set before/alongside the vector scan. | `json_extract(body,'$.path') <op> ?` over the `canonical_nodes(kind)` partition; active rows only. |
    22	| Kind of need | Retrieval-precision / scoping. | Table-stakes structured browse / query. |
    23	
    24	These are **not** the same need. One narrows *relevance ranking*; the other *enumerates by structured
    25	predicate*. A unified type must express both without collapsing either into the other's execution model.
