    12	# ADR-0.8.11 — Filter-grammar unification (G4 + G10)
    13	
    14	**Status:** proposed (Slice 0 deliverable; provisional pending HITL confirmation of
    15	Option A). This ADR **specifies** Slice 40; it ships **no** production code or test
    16	(Slice 40 implements). It closes **reserved-gap 37** (ADR-0.8.0-filter-grammar
    17	D-F3), the committed-not-optional full single-grammar unification.
    18	
    19	> **HITL decision inherited (do not re-litigate):** **Q1 = Option A** — ONE unified
    20	> typed `Filter` contract with **TWO internal compilation backends**, NOT a thin
    21	> adapter over two types. The TYPE unifies and dispatches; the data does **not**
    22	> funnel into one SQL, because the same logical predicate filters **two different
    23	> physical stores**.
    24	
    25	---
    26	
    27	## 1. Context — what is being unified, and the load-bearing finding
    28	
    29	Two filter surfaces shipped in 0.8.0 and are **both already built and SDK-exposed**:
    30	
    31	- **G10 `SearchFilter`** (shipped Slice 10): a **closed struct**
    32	  `{source_type, kind, created_after, status}`
    33	  (`src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/src/lib.rs:1487-1493`), threaded as
    34	  `Option<SearchFilter>` through `Engine::search_filtered`, compiled to an **indexed
    35	  pre-KNN `WHERE` over vec0 metadata columns** co-located with the vectors in the
    36	  `vector_default` virtual table
    37	  (`vector_filter_clause` `lib.rs:5469-5494`, `vector_filter_values`
    38	  `lib.rs:5499-5521`, `build_vector_phase1_sql` `lib.rs:5528-5545`). The pre-KNN
    39	  filter is the perf point (prune *before* the bit-KNN, not after).
    40	- **G4 `Predicate`** (shipped Slice 35 — **NOT deferred**): the closed enum
    41	  `{JsonPathEq, JsonPathCompare}` with `ComparisonOp{Gt/Gte/Lt/Lte}` and
    42	  `ScalarValue{Text/Integer/Bool}` (`lib.rs:1277-1330`), validated against the
    43	  `PREDICATE_PATH_ALLOWLIST` (`lib.rs:1310-1311`) at construction, surfaced on
    44	  `Engine::read_list(kind, predicates, limit)` (`lib.rs:501-506`), compiled to
    45	  **`json_extract(body,'$.path') <op> ?`** over `canonical_nodes` rows
    46	  (`Predicate::to_sql_clause` `lib.rs:1389-1426`; `read_list_in_tx` `lib.rs:6436-6494`).
    47	
    48	> **Load-bearing investigation finding (corrects the slice premise).** The Slice 40
    49	> brief described G4 as "NOT YET BUILT, deferred." **It is built.** `Engine::read_list`,
    50	> the `Predicate` enum + validated constructors, `read_list_in_tx`, the path
    51	> allowlist, and Py/TS SDK surfaces (`src/python/fathomdb/read.py`,
    52	> `src/ts/src/read.ts:68-72`, `_fathomdb.pyi`, with conformance + functional tests)
    53	> all exist on `0.8.11`. **Both backends already compile correctly and independently.**
    54	> This makes Slice 40 a **TYPE-unification + dispatch refactor over two shipped
    55	> compilation paths** — not a from-scratch build — which *strengthens* the
    56	> anti-laziness mandate: there is no "not-built-yet" excuse for a reserved-gap.
    57	
    58	**Why two backends, not one SQL:** the two surfaces filter **different physical
    59	stores**. G10 filters indexed metadata columns *inside the vec0 virtual table*
    60	(`source_type TEXT partition key, kind TEXT, created_at INTEGER, status TEXT` —
    61	`vector_partition_create_sql` `lib.rs:8439-8451`), pre-KNN. G4 filters JSON *inside
    62	`canonical_nodes.body`* via `json_extract` — no vectors involved. Collapsing into a
    63	single SQL would force G10 onto `json_extract` (losing its indexed pre-KNN filter — a
    64	perf regression) or G4 onto only four metadata columns (losing arbitrary json-path).
    65	So: **the TYPE unifies; the COMPILATION dispatches** to one of two backends.
    66	
    67	**Inherited (fixed inputs, not re-litigated):** ADR-0.8.0-filter-grammar D-F1..D-F5
    68	(closed grammar, no DSL, no fused, no `_unchecked`, parameterized-only, allowlisted
    69	paths, implicit-AND); slice-10 `filter=None → byte-identical 0.7.2 SQL` pin
    70	(`slice-10-design.md:122-130,204-211`); the folded `canonical_nodes(kind)` index +
    71	`superseded_at IS NULL` active-row rule.
