    74	
    75	## 1b. Requirements & User-Needs trace-up
    76	
    77	The unification is justified by **distinct User Needs**, not only code mechanics. Full
    78	trace in **`dev/design/0.8.11-analysis-G10-G4-searchfilt.md`** (Slice-0 analysis);
    79	summarized here so the design decision is grounded in the needs of the named
    80	local-first consumers (**Memex / Hermes / OpenClaw**, SQLite + sqlite-vec/FTS5).
    81	
    82	**Two needs, two stores, two execution models — both must be preserved:**
    83	
    84	- **G10 `search_filtered`** serves *"find relevant memories about X, but only from
    85	  source Y / kind K / after Z / status S"* — a **constraint on a ranked
    86	  hybrid/semantic search** (vector-KNN + RRF, optional CE-rerank), executed as an
    87	  **indexed pre-KNN** scope over vec0 metadata. It is the concrete filter mechanism
    88	  behind **F2 multi_session** (source/kind scoping) and **F3 temporal**
    89	  (`created_after`), and part of the **F0 RRF-fused stack**.
    90	- **G4 `read.list`** serves *"list all my open to-dos" / "all products rated >4★"* —
    91	  a **typed enumeration** over active `canonical_nodes(kind)` (no ranking, no
    92	  vectors), via `json_extract`. It is **F3 filtered-list**, table-stakes equality +
    93	  range.
    94	
    95	These are **not** the same need: one narrows *relevance ranking*, the other
    96	*enumerates by structured predicate*. The requirement is therefore a unified
    97	**type/contract**, explicitly **NOT** a unified SQL/storage path (this is exactly
    98	why Option A = one type, two backends, and why D3's total-dispatch + typed-rejection
    99	and D2's field matrix are load-bearing — they keep "one type" from degrading either
   100	need).
   101	
