   109	3. **0.8.15 router `constraints` block (the downstream consumer — the reason #17
   110	   exists)** — the dispatcher must reason over **one** typed-constraint surface, not
   111	   two. This forward-looking requirement is *why* "unified type" beats "thin
   112	   adapter," and confirms Option A. → §6 consequences.
