   140	
   141	---
   142	
   143	## 3. Decision (one concrete answer per question)
   144	
   145	### D1 — The unified `Filter` type (Option A: one superset, closed grammar)
   146	
   147	Slice 40 introduces ONE closed superset type. It reuses the **already-shipped**
   148	shared vocabulary (`ScalarValue`, `ComparisonOp`, `Predicate`) verbatim — no new
   149	scalar/op grammar — and adds the four G10 shorthand fields as first-class terms:
   150	
   151	```text
   152	Filter (closed)  =  { terms: Vec<FilterTerm> }      // implicit AND (inherits D-F5)
   153	
   154	FilterTerm (closed enum):
   155	  // The G10 four — "shorthand" metadata fields. Each LOWERS to the right
   156	  // physical form per backend (see D2/D3); shared across both surfaces.
   157	  SourceType(String)
   158	  Kind(String)
   159	  CreatedAfter(i64)            // created_at >= bound (unix seconds)
   160	  Status(String)
   161	  // The G4 general json-path predicate (UNCHANGED shipped grammar, D-F1):
   162	  Json(Predicate)             //  Predicate ∈ { JsonPathEq | JsonPathCompare }
   163	                              //  over PREDICATE_PATH_ALLOWLIST, parameterized
   164	```
   165	
   166	- **Closed grammar preserved (inherit ADR-0.8.0):** no DSL, no caller SQL, no
   167	  `JsonPathFused*`, no `*_unchecked`, no OR/nesting (implicit AND only); `Json`
   168	  terms are constructed ONLY through the validated `Predicate::json_path_eq` /
   169	  `Predicate::json_path_compare` (allowlist enforced at construction,
   170	  `lib.rs:1337,1349`); values always bind as `?`.
   171	- **G10's four fields are dedicated shorthand variants, not arbitrary json**, so
   172	  they can lower to the *indexed* vec0 columns on the search backend (D3). They are
   173	  NOT `Json(Predicate)` over `$.source_type` etc. — keeping them typed lets the
   174	  search backend accept them while typed-rejecting arbitrary `Json` terms.
   175	- **Naming/exhaustiveness is a closed set** — an exhaustiveness test pins
   176	  `FilterTerm` to exactly these five variants (mirrors D-F1's enumeration test).
   177	
   178	*(Slice-40 impl detail, marked TBD: whether `FilterTerm::Kind` inside `Filter` is
   179	accepted as a redundant term or constant-folded against the `read.list(kind=…)`
   180	partition argument. Both are total; pick at impl time. Not a grammar question.)*
   181	
   182	### D2 — Field-availability matrix (the load-bearing investigation)
   183	
   184	Physical stores investigated:
   185	
   186	- **vec0 `vector_default` metadata columns** (`vector_partition_create_sql`
   187	  `lib.rs:8439-8451`): `source_type` (partition key), `kind`, `created_at` (INTEGER),
   188	  `status` (TEXT). Filterable **pre-KNN** in the phase-1 `MATCH … WHERE`.
   189	- **`canonical_nodes` real columns** (`fathomdb-schema/src/lib.rs:110,198,300-301`):
   190	  `write_cursor`, `kind`, `body` (JSON), `source_id`, `logical_id`, `superseded_at`.
   191	  The only user-facing filterable real column is **`kind`**; everything else of
   192	  interest lives inside **`body` JSON** (allowlist `$.status,$.priority,$.tags,$.kind,$.created_at`,
   193	  `lib.rs:1311`). `source_type` is **NOT stored** in canonical_nodes — it is a
   194	  deterministic function of `kind` via `resolve_source_type` (`lib.rs:8640-8655`).
   195	
   196	| Filterable field | vec0 (`search_filtered`) | canonical_nodes (`read.list`) | Resolves in both? |
   197	|---|---|---|---|
   198	| **kind** | real metadata col `kind` ✓ (pre-KNN) | real col `canonical_nodes.kind` ✓ (and the partition arg itself) | **YES** |
   199	| **created_after** (`created_at`) | real metadata col `created_at` INTEGER ✓ (pre-KNN) | `json_extract(body,'$.created_at') >= ?` ✓ (`$.created_at` allowlisted) | **YES** |
   200	| **status** | real metadata col `status` TEXT ✓ (pre-KNN; empty-string sentinel, no population source yet) | `json_extract(body,'$.status') = ?` ✓ (`$.status` allowlisted) | **YES** |
   201	| **source_type** | real partition-key metadata col `source_type` ✓ (pre-KNN) | **NOT a column**; deterministic = `resolve_source_type(kind)` → **constant-fold** within the single-kind list (pass-all iff `resolve_source_type(kind)==value`, else empty) | **YES** (derived) |
   202	| **general json-path body** (`$.priority`, `$.tags`, …) | **NOT a vec0 metadata column** → would need post-KNN `json_extract` → **TYPED-REJECT** (preserve pre-KNN guarantee) | `json_extract(body,'$.path') <op> ?` ✓ (allowlisted) | resolves only on read.list **by design** (see D3) |
   203	
   204	**Verdict:** **all four G10 shorthand fields resolve in BOTH stores.** The only
   205	nuance is `source_type`: it is not a stored column in `canonical_nodes`, but because
   206	`read.list` is always partitioned by a single `kind` and `source_type` is a pure
   207	function of `kind` (`resolve_source_type`, a 6-value-locked + `edge_fact`/`doc` map),
   208	a `SourceType` term on `read.list` **constant-folds** (the whole list shares one
   209	`source_type`). That is a clean, total resolution — **NOT** a reserved-gap trigger
   210	(D6). The general-json-path row is asymmetric *by design* (it has no vec0 home and
   211	must not be demoted), which D3 turns into a typed rejection, not a gap.
   212	
   213	### D3 — Total backend-dispatch + typed-rejection (no silent fallback, no demotion)
   214	
   215	Every `FilterTerm` has a **defined outcome in EACH surface** — either "compiles to
   216	backend X" or "typed rejection with a stated reason." There is **no silent fallback**
   217	and **no demotion** of an indexed-metadata predicate to a slow post-KNN `json_extract`.
   218	
   219	**`search_filtered` (vec0 backend — indexed pre-KNN):** accepts the **metadata
   220	subset** `{SourceType, Kind, CreatedAfter, Status}` → lowered to the existing
   221	`vector_filter_clause` / `vector_filter_values` (`lib.rs:5469-5521`), appended to the
   222	single phase-1 `MATCH … {clause} ORDER BY distance LIMIT top_k`
   223	(`build_vector_phase1_sql` `lib.rs:5528-5545`); the text branch is constrained in
   224	Rust by `text_hit_passes_filter` (`lib.rs:5556+`), exactly as today.
   225	**TYPED-REJECTS** `FilterTerm::Json(_)` with `EngineError::InvalidFilter` —
   226	reason: *"arbitrary json-path predicate not supported on search_filtered; it would
   227	require a post-KNN json_extract that defeats the indexed pre-KNN filter."* This is
   228	the explicit no-demotion guarantee.
   229	
   230	**`read.list` (canonical_nodes backend — `json_extract`):** accepts the **full**
   231	set. Lowering:
   232	
   233	- `Json(p)` → `p.to_sql_clause(param_idx)` (`lib.rs:1389-1426`), the shipped path.
   234	- `Status(s)` → `Predicate::json_path_eq("$.status", Text(s))`.
   235	- `CreatedAfter(b)` → `Predicate::json_path_compare("$.created_at", Gte, Integer(b))`.
   236	- `Kind(k)` → real-column `canonical_nodes.kind = ?` (or constant-fold vs the
   237	  partition arg — D1 impl-TBD).
   238	- `SourceType(s)` → **constant-fold** vs `resolve_source_type(kind)`: pass-all
   239	  no-op term iff equal, else compile to a guaranteed-empty result (e.g. `0=1`).
   240	  Never a per-row `json_extract` (the column does not exist in body).
   241	
   242	Both lowerings keep the inherited invariants: parameterized values only, allowlisted
   243	paths only, `superseded_at IS NULL` + `logical_id IS NOT NULL` + `json_valid(body)`
   244	guards on read.list (`lib.rs:6453-6459`), `canonical_nodes(kind)` index drives the
   245	scan.
   246	
   247	### D4 — Backward compat: shipped SDK shapes re-expressed as sugar, no behavior change
   248	
   249	The public, shipped SDK types stay **byte-shape-accepted**:
   250	
   251	- **`SearchFilter{source_type,kind,created_after,status}`** (Rust `lib.rs:1487-1493`;
   252	  Py `types.py:111-127`; TS `index.ts:118-123`; Py/TS napi lowering
   253	  `fathomdb-py/src/lib.rs:850,1422`) → becomes **sugar** that lowers to
   254	  `Filter{terms: [SourceType?, Kind?, CreatedAfter?, Status?]}` (only present fields).
   255	  `Engine::search_filtered(query, Option<SearchFilter>)` keeps its signature;
   256	  internally it builds the unified `Filter` and dispatches to the vec0 backend.
   257	- **`Predicate` / `read.list`** (Py `read.py`; TS `read.ts:68-72`) → lowers to
   258	  `Filter{terms: [Json(p), …]}` and dispatches to the canonical_nodes backend.
   259	- **Byte-identity pin holds:** `SearchFilter::is_unfiltered()` / `filter=None`
   260	  (`lib.rs:1499-1504`) ⇒ empty `terms` ⇒ empty `{filter_clause}` ⇒ the phase-1 SQL

